The paper deals with the problem of finding matchings with high expected reward and low risk in uncertain graph and hypergraph databases. This problem is relevant to several applications such as querying sensor networks, analyzing protein-protein interaction networks, online dating, kidney exchanges, and team formation. The paper introduces a novel formulation for this problem and provides efficient approximation algorithms for uncertain weighted graphs and hypergraphs. The paper also tests the algorithms on synthetic experiments and provides an application for team recommendations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with optimization problems and approximation algorithms. The sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely as the paper discusses applications related to network analysis and team formation.
